The paper deals with the development of an autonomous system for luggage scanning using X-ray imagery. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks for object recognition and the extraction of contour-based transitional information. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for the recognition of suspicious items, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with security concerns related to aviation, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves the use of X-ray scans, which makes it relevant to the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
